The paper deals with real-time search algorithms and heuristics, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) for path planning and navigation. The paper also discusses the implementation of these algorithms, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents theoretical properties of the algorithms, which could be considered as machine learning (cs.LG).
